article.headline: Zavecz scores 14 points to pace No. 22 Wyoming vs. N.M.
article.linkText: Sisk FTs ice Wyoming victory over New Mexico
article.story:
ALBUQUERQUE N.M. (AP) -- Hanna Zavecz scored 14 points and Dominique Sisk swished four free throws in the final 21 seconds, leading Wyoming (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) to a 58-52 win over New Mexico on Wednesday night.

Jodi Bolerjack added 11 points as the Cowgirls (13-1), playing the Mountain West opener for both schools, won their seventh straight game and escaped The Pit with a victory for the first time since 1995.

Dionne Marsh had 24 points and seven rebounds for New Mexico (8-6), which lost for the fourth time in the past five games.

The Cowgirls, playing just their second game in three weeks, came out sluggish and trailed 26-20 at halftime.

By then, Marsh had 16 points but Wyoming tightened the defense on New Mexico's standout and got the offense started with an 8-4 run to open the second half. The Cowgirls led for the first time at 31-30 on Rebecca Vanderjagt's 3-pointer.

Meanwhile, the Cowgirls began double-teaming Marsh, forcing her to miss her first three field-goal attempts of the second half. Wyoming looked comfortable, leading 47-41 after two free throws by Sisk with 5:51 remaining.

But Brandi Kimble hit a 3-pointer to get the crowd fired up and Marsh bounced in a jumper with 3:52 to go, pulling New Mexico within 47-46. It was tied at 48 moments later after Kimble rebounded and found Eileen Weissmann for a layup.

The teams traded free throws, and it was tight down the stretch until Sisk's free throws with 21.6 seconds remaining put Wyoming ahead 56-52. She hit another pair with 12.6 seconds to go, sealing the win.
